<HEAD>Eighty-Eight Passengers, Eight Crew Members To Be Checked For Radiation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Officials found a damaged container carrying
radioactive material on a Mexicana Airlines plane Saturday and were
checking the passengers and crew for contamination, police said.
   Residue from a package of molypentachloride, a corrossive that
emits low-level beta radiation, was found in the cargo hold,
according to fire officials.
   Flight 820 from Acapulco was carrying 88 passengers and eight
crew members.
   While in flight, the pilot of the Boeing 727 radioed to Mexicana
Airlines officials that there was a problem with the container and
airline officials contacted Philadelphia police, said Cpl. Andrew
Chowmentowski.
   The incident was under investigation.
