<HEAD>16 Die From Food Poisoning in Remote Chinese Province</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sixteen Chinese laborers died last month after
eating industrial salt at a construction site canteen in the far
northwest province of Xinjiang, according to a local newspaper.
   Another 25 laborers received food poisoning in the April 25
incident in Jeminay county, 280 miles north of the provincial
capital of Urumqi, but were out of danger, according to the May 1
issue of Xinjiang Daily.
   Xinjiang is an autonomous region of the Moslem Uygur minority,
but the report said all of the poisoned workers were ethnic Han
Chinese.
   The story did not say how the salt wound up in the canteen and
its food. Authorities were investigating the incident.
