<FIRST>r i AM-Germany-OilSpill     05-07 0124</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Germany-Oil Spill,0127</SECOND>
<HEAD>Oil Spill On Rhine Moving Toward Netherlands</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DUESSELDORF, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 19-mile-long oil slick was
flowing down the Rhine River toward the Netherlands on Sunday, a
government official said.
   Johannes Winkel, a state spokesman in Duesseldorf, said West
German authorities issued an international pollution alert and
notified Dutch authorities that the spill was approaching their
territory.
   He said the spill apparently was caused by an unidentified ship
discharging its diesel fuel waste on Saturday night. Winkel did not
know how much oil had spilled, but he said the thin slick posed no
danger to the environment.
   It is illegal in West Germany to pump waste into a river, and
ships are supposed to dump it into dockside containers.
</TEXT>
