<HEAD>Five Gunmen Kill Ex-Convict in Hospital</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CATANIA, Sicily (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Five gunmen burst into a hospital and
shot to death a 36-year-old man recovering from gunshot wounds
suffered in an ambush, the Italian news agency ANSA said.
   The men overpowered a guard, entered the hospital room and fired
at least 30 pistol shots at Francesco Cazzetta, ANSA said.
   Six other patients, as well as Cazzetta's brother, witnessed the
killing but were not injured in the hail of gunfire, the agency
said.
   Cazzetta, an ex-convict who had been imprisoned for drug
trafficking, was wounded Friday when two gunmen armed with rifles
ambushed his car.
