<SECOND>AM-Space Shuttle-Coverage,0131</SECOND>
<HEAD>Networks to Cover Shuttle Landing Live</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Space Shuttle</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   CBS, NBC, and Cable News Network plan to provide
live coverage Monday of the landing of the space shuttle Atlantis.
   ABC's coverage plans were incomplete Sunday. The network will
decide whether to cover the landing closer to touchdown time, said
spokeswoman Elaine Adde.
   CBS plans to go live five minutes before touchdown. CBS
correspondent David Dow will be reporting from Edwards Air Force
Base, Calif., and Dan Rather will anchor in New York, said Donna
Dees of CBS.
   No details were available on CNN and NBC's coverage plans.
   The shuttle is expected to touch down at Edwards Air Force Base
in the Mojave Desert at 12:43 p.m. PDT (3:43 p.m. EDT).
</TEXT>
